## Module 9: Moderation APIs

All endpoints require authentication via `Authorization: Bearer <jwt_token>` header.  
Access: Any authenticated role (USER, ASSOCIATE, ADMIN).

---

### 9.1 Block User

**Endpoint:** `POST /api/v1/users/{id}/block`

| Parameter | In   | Type | Description                 |
| --------- | ---- | ---- | --------------------------- |
| [id](file:///c:/Users/yamit/Downloads/Desktop/livanaFinalbackend/backend-services/src/handlers/listing.rs#301-372)      | path | UUID | ID of the user to block     |

**Headers:**

```
Authorization: Bearer <jwt_token>
```

**Request Body:** _None_

**Success Response** `200 OK`:

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "User blocked successfully",
  "data": {}
}
```

> **Restrictions:**
> - A user cannot block themselves â†’ returns `400 Bad Request`
> - Blocking an already-blocked user is idempotent (returns success)

---

### 9.2 Report Entity

**Endpoint:** `POST /api/v1/report`

**Headers:**

```
Authorization: Bearer <jwt_token>
Content-Type: application/json
```

**Request Body:**

```json
{
  "entity_type": "PROPERTY",
  "entity_id": "b3f2c5a1-7e4d-4a89-9c12-3d5e6f7a8b9c",
  "reason": "Listing contains misleading photos and incorrect pricing."
}
```

| Field         | Type   | Required | Description                                         |
| ------------- | ------ | -------- | --------------------------------------------------- |
| `entity_type` | string | Yes      | One of: `USER`, `PROPERTY`, `COMMUNITY`, `POST`     |
| `entity_id`   | UUID   | Yes      | ID of the entity being reported                     |
| `reason`      | string | Yes      | Reason for the report                               |

**Success Response** `201 Created`:

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Report submitted successfully",
  "data": {
    "report_id": "a1b2c3d4-5e6f-7a8b-9c0d-1e2f3a4b5c6d",
    "status": "PENDING_REVIEW"
  }
}
```

