## Module 10: Vibe API (Shared Apartment Matchmaking)

All endpoints require authentication via `Authorization: Bearer <jwt_token>` header.  
Access: Any authenticated role (USER, ASSOCIATE, ADMIN).

---

### 10.1 Send Vibe

**Endpoint:** `POST /api/v1/vibes`

**Headers:**

```
Authorization: Bearer <jwt_token>
Content-Type: application/json
```

**Request Body:**

```json
{
  "target_user_id": "d4e5f6a7-0b1c-4d2e-8f9a-0b1c2d3e4f5a"
}
```

| Field            | Type | Required | Description                        |
| ---------------- | ---- | -------- | ---------------------------------- |
| `target_user_id` | UUID | Yes      | ID of the user to send a vibe to   |

**Success Response** `201 Created`:

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Vibe sent successfully",
  "data": {
    "vibe_id": "e5f6a7b8-1c2d-4e3f-9a0b-1c2d3e4f5a6b",
    "sender_id": "c4d5e6f7-8a9b-4c0d-1e2f-3a4b5c6d7e8f",
    "target_user_id": "d4e5f6a7-0b1c-4d2e-8f9a-0b1c2d3e4f5a",
    "status": "PENDING"
  }
}
```

> **Restrictions:**
> - A user cannot send a vibe to themselves â†’ `400 Bad Request`
> - Duplicate pending vibes are handled gracefully (returns existing vibe ID)

---

### 10.2 Accept Vibe

**Endpoint:** `POST /api/v1/vibes/{id}/accept`

| Parameter | In   | Type | Description               |
| --------- | ---- | ---- | ------------------------- |
| [id](file:///c:/Users/yamit/Downloads/Desktop/livanaFinalbackend/backend-services/src/handlers/listing.rs#301-372)      | path | UUID | ID of the vibe to accept  |

**Headers:**

```
Authorization: Bearer <jwt_token>
```

**Request Body:** _None_

**Success Response** `200 OK`:

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Vibe accepted. It's a match!",
  "data": {}
}
```

> **Security:** Only the `target_user_id` of the vibe can accept it â†’ others get `403 Forbidden`.  
> Already-accepted or already-rejected vibes return `400 Bad Request`.

